  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of the vertex attributes, must be serializable
    E - the type of the edge attributes, must be serializable

    public class BigGraph<V extends java.io.Serializable,E extends java.io.Serializable>
extends AbstractBigGraph<dht.ObjectDHT<V>,EdgeObjectAttributeTable<E>>
    A graph with objects as vertex attributes and edge attributes. Such a graph can be created from a DataSet, or a BigAdjacencyTable to set the topology, together with an ObjectDHT to set the initial vertex attributes. A graph is a specific distributed object (LiveDistributedObject) , spread over a set of cluster nodes. As all distributed objects a graph has a unique ID to identify it among all other distributed objects.
